        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 21 at 2:38PM CDT by NWS Topeka KS</headline>
        <description>At 237 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Formoso, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Strong wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Belleville, Scandia, Courtland, and Republic.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
